[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating test strategies**\n\nI’m considering whether to add a second test using classloader fallback with a custom resource that returns an actual stream. I'm unsure if we should maintain the positive class resource for generating metadata since the user mentioned remaining resource call sites. It might be better to focus on a supported positive resource lookup through the regular public API. However, the previous attempt didn’t address the native failure, though the `new FileUtil.FileAccessRes` positive native test with generated metadata passes. Local native issues could complicate things.\n\n**Considering metadata generation**\n\nI’m worried about potential failures in the native setup if metadata isn’t generated correctly. The test agent will handle the generation, but I’m thinking about the local native instance—it’s not working out, and maybe we need an external workflow after new tests. Generally, the flow is from javaTest with the agent to generated metadata, followed by nativeTest. I feel good that our resource access will generate the necessary metadata for `org/hsqldb/lib/tar/rb.properties`, enabling native to pass.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0d3e671c616e7317016a1165f9c6908192a31b2037c1c4130d\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqEWYiQcqqLjWfspc0v2biHM5_SnvPi4H6X-zuTiALsQUFe4PXYz0B0ld3tBZ1qS2Yx0Uwg5prEWkwdql_oah1UAwM_b5_1nqkt8a5onr4mvVmzTa6kIZVxAdVcXcNUSGIt3RFh4UszfWAuiI5C9nR7oEuEPwu6b6pp_bp0xU332o_uHNKD8XqqqpMkjHUVDogyhGSjlYYKUY0sx_NEalo_fiSjCZsu5p2WI1blyYPVTqF-U7ivqEbCZCIBUykgNpxd9wG_0oQ1Z0PNyCqRXlZO7jc7GMpjSC6-VK050-JxnyQ5Z92a3KO7i5c2Rn9RySO2M-0Qffh-X26_WQQ7x6b-pi3JXFTZRVS72CKXntinzqb3xU4fOPAEytcbgdGdVY4b_jgXNym2Exn2j9E81iu6IznslQLrim9grC5to2O0hn2gEjKscFqj5PyAw1h-DIbB-WWCN7ytPgcyI0YuT4EnKJ2AT2Uu4N53PVy6TkI5kJQ3kMSwAb_WxgEI7VbNlpkoLqSMcilh0cs0aoqNIJwUKO4ka63ymspgWvTrseJyLF7g1gv7V2DVYXhHmUYpT9N8MPk5orcaNri3TD6o6kcsG